<h1>Tools for Linux based routers</h1>

<h2>mkfirm - create firmware files for BRN bootloader</h2>

Compile <a href="mkfirm.c">mkfirm.c</a> on your host platform and
use it to create firmware images for router devices with a
Broadnet bootloader.

<h2>sx-at - Xmodem protocol for routers</h2>

Many router devices allow firmware uploads via serial port and
Xmodem protocol.<p>

Microsoft Windows users can use Hyperterm - it works.<p>

With Linux, one could use minicom with the standard Xmodem program sx,
but sx does not really work with my routers.<p>

So I looked for another Xmodem program and found sx-at91 which
works perfectly with my routers.
Compile <a href="sx-at91.c">sx-at91.c</a> and use it with minicom.

